Celery
Red Bell Pepper
Onion
Okra
Smoked sausage medallions
Shrimp
Clam/Fish Stock
Scallions
1 to 1 Veg Oil/Flour
Garlic
Thyme
Bay Leaves
Cayenne Pepper (or bebere)
Parsley

40 minute cook time. Add Sausage half way. Shrimp at end.

Heat the oil before adding the flour and after a chocoate color has been achieved, add the trinity. Add the room-temperature fish stock (made from shrimp and clam juice). Use plenty of garlic, dried thyme, and bay leaves but just 1/4 teaspoon of cayenne pepper. Add generous amounts of smoked sausage and shrimp, and finish with parsley and scallions.
